        "27": {
            "annotation": "Workflow for retrieving the IDs of contigs and CDSs of antibiotic resistance genes and filtering Prodigal output to retrieve a catalogue of antibiotic resistance genes and potential genes present on the same contig as the ARG.",
            "id": 27,
            "input_connections": {
                "ABRicate Tabular report": {
                    "id": 22,
                    "input_subworkflow_step_id": 1,
                    "output_name": "output"
                },
                "Megahit contigs": {
                    "id": 13,
                    "input_subworkflow_step_id": 3,
                    "output_name": "output"
                },
                "Prodigal Genes Sequences": {
                    "id": 15,
                    "input_subworkflow_step_id": 4,
                    "output_name": "out_file1"
                },
                "StarAMR Tabular report": {
                    "id": 20,
                    "input_subworkflow_step_id": 2,
                    "output_name": "resfinder"
                },
                "argNorm AMRFinderPlus Tabular report": {
                    "id": 24,
                    "input_subworkflow_step_id": 0,
                    "output_name": "output"
                },
                "when": {
                    "id": 11,
                    "output_name": "boolean_param"
                }
            },
            "inputs": [],
            "label": null,
            "name": "Genes catalogue AMR specific part",
            "outputs": [],
            "position": {
                "left": 3119.2333984375,
                "top": 770.433349609375
            },
            "subworkflow": {
                "a_galaxy_workflow": "true",
                "annotation": "",
                "comments": [],
                "creator": [
                    {
                        "class": "Person",
                        "email": "mailto:abromics-support@groupes.france-bioinformatique.fr",
                        "name": "ABRomics"
                    },
                    {
                        "class": "Organization",
                        "name": "abromics-consortium",
                        "url": "https://www.abromics.fr/"
                    },
                    {
                        "class": "Person",
                        "email": "mailto:hugo.lefeuvre@univ-nantes.fr",
                        "identifier": "https://orcid.org/0009-0005-6834-4058",
                        "name": "Hugo Lefeuvre"
                    }
                ],
                "format-version": "0.1",
                "license": "GPL-3.0-or-later",
                "name": "Genes catalogue AMR specific part",
                "readme": "This workflow is only activated if **the Boolean selected in the gene catalog workflow is False**, which means that the user don't want a complete gene catalog but **specific AMR**.\n\nThis workflow takes the tabular outputs from **ABRicate, starAMR, and argNorm for AMRFinderPlus** as input. It also uses the **Prodigal** output corresponding to the FASTA file of the DNA sequences of the potential genes detected.\n\nBased on the outputs from the antibiotic resistance detection tools and Prodigal, this sub-workflow has two objectives:\n\n* The workflow retrieves the IDs of the contigs on which antibiotic resistance has been detected (with the CDS information still on them),\n\nThen:\n* It retrieves all the CDSs corresponding to these ARGs and then clusters them in the main workflow\n\nAnd:\n* At the same time, it removes the CDS information and creates a single list of contig IDs.\n* It then retrieves all the CDSs that have been detected on the same contig IDs so that it can then functionally and taxonomically annotate the genes close to the ARGs in the main workflow.",
                "report": {
                    "markdown": "\n# Workflow Execution Report\n\n## Workflow Inputs\n```galaxy\ninvocation_inputs()\n```\n\n## Workflow Outputs\n```galaxy\ninvocation_outputs()\n```\n\n## Workflow\n```galaxy\nworkflow_display()\n```\n"
                },
                "steps": {
                    "0": {
                        "annotation": "",
                        "content_id": null,
                        "errors": null,
                        "id": 0,
                        "input_connections": {},
                        "inputs": [
